Ctrl-b h       # select pane L (you can use ; for this too)
Ctrl-b l       # select pane R
Ctrl-b k       # select pane U
Ctrl-b j       # select pane D
Ctrl-b "       # split up-down
Ctrl-b %       # split left-right
Ctrl-b {/}     # move panes around up/down

Ctrl-b Ctrl-6  # alternate session
Ctrl-b [       # enter copy mode
Ctrl-b s       # session list/chooser
Ctrl-b w       # window list/chooser (usually not what you want)

Ctrl-b Space   # next layout (C-Space for prev)

Ctrl-b f       # fzf based sessionizer
Ctrl-b :       # command prompt
Ctrl-b r       # reload tmux config (also C-r)
Ctrl-b d       # detach tmux client
Ctrl-b x       # kill pane menu
Ctrl-b $       # rename session (, for window but not what you want)


Copy Mode - enter with Ctrl-b [
===============================
Space         # begin selection mode (also v)
Enter         # copy-pipe and cancel (also C-j)
C-c           # cancel copy mode
C-u/C-d       # halfpage up / down
Esc           # clear selection
C-v           # rectangle toggle

Paste buffer stuff
==================
Ctrl-b =       # supposed to choose buffer?
Ctrl-b ]       # paste buffer

Resize panes with Ctrl-b and Ctrl+Arrow keys
